<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.90}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.58}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.90}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.58}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>35.02</li><li>65.04</li><li>80.75</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={7.9}^{{2}}+{8.58}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({7.9}\right)}{\left({8.58}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}={62.41}+{73.6164}-{135.564}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{111.0264}=-{135.564}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.81899619367974}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={35.015565232064}={35.02}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({35.015565232064}\right)}}}}{{5.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{7.90}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.69867033122059}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.69867033122059}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={65.039963510524}\approx{65.04}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{35.015565232064}+{65.039963510524}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={80.748722699898}\approx{80.75}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>